Maybe the solution would be to make pets con even to owner, that would fix their lower skills.<br>
<br>
I would like to see our pets be more or less immune to AEs, why not, Cleric hammers now are totaly ummune it seems. Even if that would be a little extreme I think it would be fair if they had one immunity each. Give Epic pet magic immune.<br>
<br>
All changes Cleric hammers got, Rage of Zomm should also get. Meaning, cheap mana, fast casting and recycle and totaly spellimmune. Also lower its freaking delay a bit.<br>
<br>
I would like to see our Epic item act as a pet focus, Epic is fine, but the &quot;bad&quot; part about epic is that you totaly stop using our other pets. I like to be able to use our other pets even if I get epic. So my suggestion is to make our other pets alot better in the in the areas they now good at, make all pets hit slightly hard if you wield Epic (like Staff of Elementary Master add 2pt dmg, let epic add 6pt)<br>
<br>
Let the Greater Vocerate pets get an added spellproc that fit their profil, maybe Earthpet would proc a snare spell, fire proc a good firespell (or simply cast 2 circle higher spells), make water proc a poison dot (that maybe lowered the targets str, and AC), make Air proc a 70pt DD spell with 0.5 sec stun. <br>
Make our normal pets as usefull again and in some cases, especially in groups more desirable than Epic.<br>
<br>
Change our post 50 firepet back to normal, or make it monk class.<br>
<br>
Fix Decoy spell, either scrap the pet total and if they fix firepet let this pet be a wizard pet instead. Or make it acctually work, make it CAST a AE taunt spell every 3 sec (almost as anoying as sentinel), have 10k hp, Melee for 10pt, can't be buffed (so not be able to use as MT on a mob and let mob kill itself on DS), cost 200mana and 1sec casting time. In other word .. a VERY good Decoy and nothing else.<br>
<br>
I would like to see pet get back some of their weapon proc ability, meaning it would proc a little more than it do now. Then give us a few unique weapon summonings, if possible weapons that might suck as PC weapons, but the effect could be usefull as a swap in weapon (or as pet weapon ofcourse).<br>
<br>
<br>
I also would like to see us (and maybe other petclases, atleast Beastlords) get a whole new line of pet AA skills.<br>
The skill I think we could share is skills like making pet permanent Fear immune.<br>
Give pet diffrent levels of runspeed.<br>
Give pet higher regenrate.<br>
The mage unique skills I would like to see is ofcourse some way of give pet a huge dmg and hp boost, basicly a DC for mages. I also think some commands skills like tell pet to go Defensive or Offencive, ofcourse these skills have a recycle time.<br>
<br>
<br>
There are acctaully plenty they can do to make using pets alot more fun (well funnier, I love using pets). <br>
